"{\"uid\": \"mirror.co.uk-tv-tv-news-olympics-legend-signs-up-dancing-33782623\", \"text\": \"Sir Steve Redgrave has been announced for the new series of Dancing On Ice. The Olympian becomes the third star to be confirmed for the new series, after formerThe Only Way Is EssexstarFerne McCannandThe Traitorsicon Mollie Pearce were announced for the upcoming series.  Speaking onThis Morningon Monday, September 30, Steve revealed he had signed up for the show after making an ill-timed joke. He had recorded a video for show stars Torvill and Dean as they marked their 40th anniversary from their Olympics win as he had also won a medal that same four decades ago. At the time, he joked about them getting him on the show and that's exactly what they did.  He told hostsBen ShephardandCat Deeley: \\\"People are rowers because they can not catch or throw. Rowing is a very coordinated sport, but it ends up with people not being very coordinated because they have done the same movements over and over again.\\\"  Training begins next week after a group masterclass on Tuesday, and it will be a few weeks on from that that Steve will meet his professional skating partner. He also revealed he is having a special pair of skates made to fit his size 12 feet.  OnGood Morning Britaintoday, Ferne McCann confirmed her reality show was ending, before adding her excitement about joining Dancing On Ice. She told hostsSusanna Reidand Ed Balls: \\\"I am doingDancing On Ice! So excited! I have done Winter Wonderland with the children, but the penguins the kids have got - I am crunched over them!  \\\"I am looking forward to it; it's going to be a huge challenge. But the glitz and the glam, it's going to be brilliant.\\\"  The Traitors star Mollie Pearce was also announced for the new series after she lost out on the prize money on theBBCshow to friend Harry Clark, who betrayed her at the last moment. Speaking of joining Dancing On Ice during an appearance on ITV's Lorraine, she shared her hopes for the new series. She said: \\\"It will be fun, I want to challenge myself, I am ready for the challenge.\\\"  Jayne Torvill and Christopher Dean are expected to return for the new series, which kicks off in January 2025. Oti Mabuse and Ashley Banjo are also likely to return as judges alongside the skating legends.  Last year, the show was hosted byHolly Willoughbyand Stephen Mulhern, who stepped in as a permanent host whenPhillip Schofieldexited the show. It has yet to be confirmed whether both Holly and Stephen will be back for the new series.  This Morning is on ITV1 weekdays at 10am and on ITVX  AtReach and across our entitieswe and our partners use information collected through cookies and other identifiers from your device to improve experience on our site, analyse how it is used and to show personalised advertising. You can opt out of the sale or sharing of your data, at any time clicking the \\\"Do Not Sell or Share my Data\\\" button at the bottom of the webpage. Please note that your preferences are browser specific. Use of our website and any of our services represents your acceptance of the use ofcookiesand consent to the practices described in ourPrivacy NoticeandTerms and Conditions.\"}"